Teatime on the Spalenberg

   In our lobby, overlooking on the Spalenberg, we serve canapés, scones,
   sweet pastries and a selection of aromatic tea variations from London
   Tea on the Spalenberg every day from 14.30pm to 16.30pm.

   Choose between:
     * Tea Time "Classic"
     * Tea Time "Deluxe"with a glas of champagne from Louis Roederer

   more details

Hotel Basel - urban tradition

   Our modern and urban hotel, located in the heart of beautiful Basel,
   houses a infrastructure with new renovated rooms and offers everything
   the discerning guest desires.

   Hotel Basel is situated in Basel’s old city, surrounded by handsome
   historic buildings, and located just above Market Square (Marktplatz)
   and the town hall (Rathaus). Our central location in the pedestrian
   area allows you to enjoy Basel’s sightseeing attractions or do some
   leisurely window-shopping on foot.


    Business people, tourists and families will enjoy the central
    location. Whether you want enjoy the theatre, visit a museum or go on
    a shopping spree – you can easily walk to all the hot spots in no
    time.

   We offer all guests shopping benefits in over 30 shops around the
   hotel.
   Please note that despite or location in the pedestrian area, guests are
   allowed to drive directly to the hotel’s front door (see arrival
   directions), for GPS enter location “Fischmarkt.”

   The city itself as well as Hotel Basel is always worth a stay!

   Esther Brühwiler and her team


   Esther Bruehwiler small
